    <h1>Architecture: Subdomains, Colleges, and Scholarships</h1>

    <p>Architecture is a multifaceted field encompassing various subdomains. Here's an overview:</p>

    <div class="subdomain">
        <h2>1. Residential Architecture</h2>
        <p><strong>Explanation:</strong> Focuses on designing homes, from single-family houses to multi-dwelling apartments. It involves understanding client needs, creating functional layouts, and ensuring aesthetic appeal.</p>
        <p><strong>Importance:</strong> Addresses the fundamental human need for shelter and comfort, creating spaces where people live and thrive.</p>
        <p><strong>Demand:</strong> Consistently high due to population growth and the ongoing need for housing.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="subdomain">
        <h2>2. Commercial Architecture</h2>
        <p><strong>Explanation:</strong> Deals with designing commercial buildings like offices, retail stores, and shopping malls. It emphasizes functionality, branding, and customer experience.</p>
        <p><strong>Importance:</strong> Shapes business environments, contributing to economic activity and urban development.</p>
        <p><strong>Demand:</strong> Fluctuates with economic conditions but remains significant due to business expansion and development.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="subdomain">
        <h2>3. Urban Planning</h2>
        <p><strong>Explanation:</strong> Focuses on the design and development of cities and towns, considering factors like zoning, transportation, and public spaces.</p>
        <p><strong>Importance:</strong> Creates sustainable and livable urban environments, addressing issues like congestion and pollution.</p>
        <p><strong>Demand:</strong> Increasing due to rapid urbanization and the need for efficient urban management.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="subdomain">
        <h2>4. Landscape Architecture</h2>
        <p><strong>Explanation:</strong> Involves designing outdoor spaces, including parks, gardens, and public landscapes, integrating natural elements with built environments.</p>
        <p><strong>Importance:</strong> Enhances environmental quality, promotes recreation, and creates aesthetically pleasing outdoor spaces.</p>
        <p><strong>Demand:</strong> Growing due to increased awareness of environmental sustainability and the importance of green spaces.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="subdomain">
        <h2>5. Interior Architecture</h2>
        <p><strong>Explanation:</strong> Focuses on the interior design of buildings, including space planning, material selection, and lighting design.</p>
        <p><strong>Importance:</strong> Creates functional and comfortable interior spaces, enhancing the user experience.</p>
        <p><strong>Demand:</strong> Stable, with ongoing demand for creating efficient and appealing interior environments.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="subdomain">
        <h2>6. Conservation Architecture</h2>
        <p><strong>Explanation:</strong> Deals with preserving and restoring historic buildings and sites, balancing preservation with modern use.</p>
        <p><strong>Importance:</strong> Protects cultural heritage and preserves architectural landmarks for future generations.</p>
        <p><strong>Demand:</strong> Increasing, driven by a growing appreciation for historical preservation.</p>
    </div>

